comment: A set does not contain the singleton formed on it. More precisely, one can prove that a class contains the singleton formed on it if and only if it is proper and contains the "singleton formed on it", which is the empty set: ` |- -. ( { A } e. A <-> ( (/) e. A -> A e. _V ) ) ` . (Contributed by BJ, 4-Feb-2023.)
